91
00:04:02,220 --> 00:04:07,980
The pragmatic Sancho Panza then questions,

92
00:04:04,019 --> 00:04:10,980
'But do you have a reason to go mad, señor?

93
00:04:07,980 --> 00:04:12,900
What is the reason?'

94
00:04:10,980 --> 00:04:15,599
'That's the whole point,' Don Quixote replies.

95
00:04:12,900 --> 00:04:18,000
'That’s the uniqueness of the quest I've devised.

96
00:04:15,599 --> 00:04:20,519
Any knight-errant who has gone mad

97
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:23,160
for a particular reason

98
00:04:20,519 --> 00:04:26,340
neither seeks reward nor gratitude.'

96
00:04:15,599 --> 00:04:20,519
The knight-errants went mad for some reason.

97
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:23,160
He neither sought rewards nor thanks:

98
00:04:20,519 --> 00:04:26,340
the trick was to

99
00:04:23,160 --> 00:04:29,460
lose one's wits without any cause.

100
00:04:26,340 --> 00:04:31,979
And as we will soon see,

101
00:04:29,460 --> 00:04:33,300
these echoes in

102
